JOHANNESBURG - Pioneer Foods says a stronger rand and crop shortfalls have affected the company s profits.The makers of food products such as Sasko bread and Weetbix on Monday reported a 47 percent fall in headline earnings in the six months to March.The group's turnover increased by only two percent.READ: Pioneer Foods consumes UK's StreamfoodsThe company says its groceries performance failed to impress, with its beverages business below par.The cost of goods sold increased by 10 percent due to higher input costs.Gross profit decreased by 16 percent to R2.6-billion.Pioneer Foods says it anticipates an improvement in performance in the second half of the financial year. eNCA